The '''A512''' is an [[A roads in Great Britain|A road]] entirely in [[Leicestershire]], [[United Kingdom|UK]]. It links the primary destination of [[Loughborough]] with the [[M1 motorway|M1]], [[A42 road (England)|A42 road]], and the town of [[Ashby de la Zouch]].

The road begins just outside Loughborough Town Centre, near to The Rushes {{nowrap|({{coord|52.7724|-1.2078|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline|name=A512 road (eastern end)}}).}} It heads out of town, crossing the A6004 Epinal Way and passing [[Loughborough University]]. On leaving the town, there is a short dual carriageway section, leading to the junction with Snells Nook Lane to Nanpanton and Woodhouse.

After this junction, the road returns to single carriageway for about {{convert|1|mi}}, to Junction 23 of the M1. 

At this junction, much of the traffic from Loughborough turns off, and it is a much quieter A512 that enters [[Shepshed]]. After Shepshed, the road passes through Northern [[Charnwood Forest]], near the villages of Peggs Green, [[Thringstone]], [[Griffydam]], [[Belton, Leicestershire|Belton]] and [[Osgathorpe]]. Shortly before Ashby it passes [[Coleorton Hall]] on the right &ndash; a house which has played host to Scott, Wordsworth, Coleridge and others &ndash; now converted to apartments.

The road ends at the junction with the A42 and [[A511 road|A511]] (formerly the [[A50 road|A50]]), on the edge of Ashby {{nowrap|({{coord|52.7491|-1.4456|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline|name=A512 road (western end)}}).}}

The A512 is {{convert|11|mi}} long, with the M1 junction {{convert|8|mi}} from the southern end.

